<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,271,223,249]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Notes.</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter, E." box="[281,441,223,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="209 - 224" refId="ref23239" refString="Reitter, E. (1902) Verschiedenes uber die Coleopteren der Tenebrioniden-Abtheilung Helopina. Deutsche Entomologische Zeitschrift, 1901, 209 - 224." type="journal article" year="1902">Reitter (1902)</bibRefCitation>
listed “ 
<specimenCount box="[533,570,223,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="male">1♂</specimenCount>
<specimenCount box="[570,587,223,249]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
” in the original description, but I suggest that it is a misprint, because he described only male characters and only 
<specimenCount box="[615,717,259,285]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="male">one male</specimenCount>
is deposited in HNHM. In the same paper, he always indicated whether a character refers to a female or a male for other species and wrote “ 
<specimenCount box="[1015,1055,295,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="male">1 ♂</specimenCount>
und 
<specimenCount box="[1111,1131,295,321]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="female">♀</specimenCount>
”.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="7" pageNumber="458" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="7.[151,1437,150,573]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,353,330,356]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Distribution.</emphasis>
<collectingCountry box="[360,405,331,357]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Iran</collectingCountry>
(Talysh). Extensive collecting efforts (more than 190 years) have not produced any records of this species in the territory of the modern Azerbaijani part of Talysh, where only 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Menetries" baseAuthorityYear="1832" box="[1107,1275,367,393]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Euboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="quadricollis">
<emphasis box="[1107,1275,367,393]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">E. quadricollis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
was collected in alpine meadows. In conclusion, I’m sure that the species occurs Iranian part of the Talysh Mountains and can be excluded from the Azerbaijani faunistic lists. 
<bibRefCitation author="Reitter, E." box="[667,826,439,465]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="1 - 44" refId="ref23264" refString="Reitter, E. (1922) Bestimmungstabelle der palaearktischen Helopinae (Col. Tenebrionidae). Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 39, 1 - 44 + 113 - 171. https: // doi. org / 10.5962 / bhl. part. 2572" type="journal article" year="1922">Reitter (1922)</bibRefCitation>
also recorded 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[994,1156,439,465]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Euboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prometheus">
<emphasis box="[994,1156,439,465]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">E. prometheus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for Astrabad (Now Gorgan, 
<collectingCountry box="[204,253,475,501]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Iran</collectingCountry>
), probably confusing it with 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="G. S. Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[570,725,475,500]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Euboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorganicus">
<emphasis box="[570,725,475,500]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">E. gorganicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Kuhnelt, W." box="[738,909,474,501]" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" pagination="65 - 102" refId="ref22206" refString="Kuhnelt, W. (1957) Ergebnisse der Osterreichischen Iran-Expedition 1949 / 50. Die Tenebrioniden Irans. Sitzungsberichte der Osterreichischen Akademie der Wissenschaften, Mathematisch-Naturwissenschaftliche Klasse, 166, 65 - 102." type="journal article" year="1957">Kühnelt (1957)</bibRefCitation>
recorded 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[1018,1178,475,501]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Euboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prometheus">
<emphasis box="[1018,1178,475,501]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">E. prometheus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from the Caucasus and Central 
<collectingCountry box="[240,289,511,537]" name="Iran" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Iran</collectingCountry>
; the second locality is erroneous. Abdurakhamanov &amp; Nabozhenko (2011) partly mixed 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="Reitter" baseAuthorityYear="1902" box="[1276,1437,511,537]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Euboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="prometheus">
<emphasis box="[1276,1437,511,537]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">E. prometheus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with females of 
<taxonomicName baseAuthorityName="G. S. Medvedev" baseAuthorityYear="1976" box="[332,488,547,572]" class="Insecta" family="Tenebrionidae" genus="Euboeus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="7" pageNumber="458" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorganicus">
<emphasis box="[332,488,547,572]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">E. gorganicus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and erroneously recorded it for 
<collectingRegion box="[849,1098,547,573]" country="Iran" name="Mazandaran" pageId="7" pageNumber="458">Mazandaran Province</collectingRegion>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
